Dear Hiring Team, 

It is with great pleasure that I submit my candidacy for the *Development Engineer I* position with *Tyson Foods*. I bring over three years of professional experience in full-stack software development, distributed systems, and automation, along with a strong academic foundation as a Master of Science in Computer Science graduate from Pace University, NY.

Through my experience across multiple engineering roles, I have built and delivered production-grade backend systems that directly reflect *the rigorous software solutions design, cross-functional collaboration, and end-to-end testing across distributed systems this position demands*. As a Software Engineer at Sperse, I implemented an MCP AI interaction layer that translates natural-language intents into validated tool calls across 1,000+ platform endpoints — requiring rigorous API contract design, input validation, and safe execution across a distributed surface. To ensure operational stability, I implemented a full observability stack using Langfuse and LangSmith for tracing and structured logging, which has been critical for troubleshooting and resolving software defects. Prior to Sperse, as a Software Engineer at Qualitest, I contributed to the backbone infrastructure that thousands of users rely on daily. I designed and developed a cloud-agnostic Storage Service using Python, PostgreSQL, and Redis that seamlessly handles file operations across AWS S3 and Google Cloud Storage through unit and integration testing — giving me direct, hands-on experience with cloud-native, multi-environment backend design. I also contributed to an Identity & Access Management platform built with Java, Spring Boot, and AWS, ensuring software security and compliance with industry standards, and developed backend workflows using AWS Step Functions to manage long-running data jobs and prevent system timeouts — both of which required *the kind of systems-level thinking and operational stability focus this role demands*. Together, these roles have prepared me to *contribute meaningfully to the team's core engineering responsibilities, from designing robust software solutions to improving development processes*.

My academic research and collaborative experience have given me a rigorous foundation in technical communication and disciplined problem-solving — skills that translate directly into *the safety-first culture and commitment to integrity this team values*. As an AI Researcher at the Pace Artificial Intelligence Lab, I managed the full lifecycle of complex model training runs on an HPC cluster, ensuring both performance and security. Beyond technical execution, I led workshops for 50+ students, where I was responsible for articulating complex technical concepts clearly and providing constructive feedback — directly mirroring *the collaborative meetings and technical documentation responsibilities central to this role*. This experience has shaped me into an engineer who builds with rigor and communicates with clarity, both of which I would bring to *Tyson Foods and its mission*.

I have always been passionate about *bringing high-quality food to every table safely and sustainably* and envision myself contributing my talent to the furthering of *raising expectations for how much the world can achieve in creating a better, more sustainable food future*. I would love to discuss my interest in this position with your team and can be reached at #ph or #eml. Thank you for your time and consideration, I look forward to connecting!

